    <custom_item>
      type        : FILE_CONTENT_CHECK
      description : "WG345 A22 - The web server must remove all export ciphers from the cipher suite."
      info        : "During the initial setup of a Transport Layer Security (TLS) connection to the web server, the client sends a list of supported cipher suites in order of preference.  The web server will reply with the cipher suite it will use for communication from the client list.  If an attacker can intercept the submission of cipher suites to the web server and place, as the preferred cipher suite, a weak export suite, the encryption used for the session becomes easy for the attacker to break, often within minutes to hours."
      solution    : "Update the cipher specification string for all enabled SSLCipherSuite directives to include !EXPORT."
      reference   : "800-171|3.13.8,800-53|SC-8,CAT|II,CSF|PR.DS-2,CSF|PR.DS-5,ISO/IEC-27001|A.13.2.3,ITSG-33|SC-8,NESA|T7.4.1,NIAv2|NS5d,NIAv2|NS6b,Rule-ID|SV-75159r1_rule,STIG-ID|WG345_A22,SWIFT-CSCv1|2.1,TBA-FIISB|29.1,Vuln-ID|V-60707"
      see_also    : "https://iasecontent.disa.mil/stigs/zip/U_Apache_2-2_UNIX_V1R11_STIG.zip"
      file        : "/etc/httpd/conf.d/ssl.conf"
      regex       : "^[\\s]*SSLCipherSuite[\\s]*"
      expect      : "^[\\s]*SSLCipherSuite[\\s]+.*(!EXP|!EXPORT).*$"
